<h2 id="don-t-blow-up-on-an-empty-request-body">Don't Blow up on an Empty Request Body! <a class="headerlink" href="reuse-consistency#don-t-blow-up-on-an-empty-request-body" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>One other little detail here is that if the request body is blank this is
going to blow up with an invalid request body format because <code>json_decode</code>
is going to return <code>null</code>. Now technically sending a blank request is not
invalid json so I  don't want to blow up in that way. This doesn't affect
anything now but it's planning for the future. So if <code>!$request-&gt;getContent()</code>,
then just set $data to an array. Else, we'll do all of our logic down here
that actually decodes the json:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="97c11d81e7">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
