<p>This comes from a component inside of Symfony that Silex uses. It's an object
but it acts just like an array with some extra nice methods. Let me show
you what I mean, back in <code>TokenController</code> instead of using it like an array
we can now say <code>$data-&gt;get()</code> and if that key doesn't exist it's not going
to throw some bad index warning. We can also use the second argument as the
default value:</p>
